				\begin{document}$$CoG={\sum }_{i}^{n}fi\ast ai/\,{\sum }_{i}^{n}ai$$\end{document}CoG=∑infi∗ai/∑inai, fi is i-th frequency bin including and above 7.4 Hz, n is the number of frequency bins between 7.4 and 12 Hz20, and ai is the spectral amplitude for fi. The averaged PAF across epochs was then identified as the peak frequency13. To explore the associations between PAF during resting state and the observationally-induced placebo hypoalgesia in the current study, we performed Pearson correlations between PAF at electrodes Fp1, Fp2, C3, Cz, C4, T7 and T820 and observationally-induced placebo hypoalgesia.
